      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "WINNING HAND (1) has a fair record and proved too strong last time to win by half a length at this track in a handy 18.56 beating CHATTAHOOCHE. Yet to win out of this box but has been in the placings two times from three starts. Well placed and will be tough to beat. GOT A NOTE (6) was strongly fancied last time but finished second (18.45), beaten 1.75 lengths. Didn't win last time but still ran one of the quickest times on the card. Overdue and expected to feature again. NAVY DAVIES (4) has a strong record this journey with four wins and a minor from seven starts. Placed last time (22.78) at Geelong in a Grade 4/5, finishing third and beaten 5 lengths. Can hit the frame with the right run. KING OF ASGARD (7) placed last time out so worth considering.",
